### 4. CULTURAL CONTEXT MISSING
**Problems**:
- No mention of optics-ready (critical 2026 CCW trend)
- No state law awareness (10-round cap in CA, NY, WA, IL)
- No aftermarket ecosystem (Shield Arms S15 for Glock 43X)
**Root cause**: Writer prompt has no cultural awareness rules for target_country.
**Fix**:
- [system_write_from_blueprint_review.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_write_from_blueprint_review.txt) — add section:
```
CULTURAL AWARENESS ({target_country}):
- US: Acknowledge state-specific magazine capacity restrictions (10-round states: CA, NY, WA, IL, etc.). Use phrasing like "If you're in a free state, you get X rounds..."
- US: For CCW/carry guns in 2026+, ALWAYS mention optics-ready capability (red dot cut)
- US: When comparing against a benchmark, acknowledge its aftermarket ecosystem (e.g., Shield Arms S15 for Glock 43X). Ignoring it destroys credibility.
- US: Be aware of brand perception (Turkish imports have QC stigma, European brands carry prestige)
```
- [system_extract_blueprint_review.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_extract_blueprint_review.txt) — add field: "aftermarket_ecosystem" per product

